author: News Tribune
title: Jefferson City in cross country districts
text:
Jefferson City in cross country districts Jays and Lady Jays advance to sectional championships Share 
LEBANON, Mo. — The Jefferson City Jays and Lady Jays both finished second Saturday in the Class 4 District 5 Championships. 
With their finishes, the Jays and Lady Jays both advance to next Saturday’s sectional championships. The top four team finishers at sectional advance to state. 
On the boys side, Jefferson City teammates Saxon Teubner (16:08.64) and Jackson Schwartz (16:11.21) finished second and third, respectively. 
Also for the Jays, Cole Biesemeyer came in 13th (16:43.99), while Landon Dunlap was 18th (17:05.61) and Thomas Nield (17:08.08) were 18th and 19th, respectively. 
Courtney Fitch (22nd, 17:15.58) and Brendan Bena (32nd, 17:48.30) rounded out Jefferson City finishers. 
West Plains took boys team honors with 42 points. Jefferson City finished second with 55, while Kickapoo (66) and Glendale (110) also claimed sectional spots. There were 11 teams in the event. 
On the girls side, the Lady Jays got top-10 finishes from Lindsey Biesemeyer (sixth, 19:57.61) and Caitlin Ruth (ninth, 20:00.08). Ryan Esterline was 16th (20:11.49, while Brianne Bechtel (20:24.30) and Kayelee Payton (20:24.55) were 20th and 21st, respectively. 
Mackenzie Gourley (25th, 20:30.89) and Syleste Martinez (29th, 20:45.64) rounded out Jefferson City’s finishers. 
West Plains was first as a team with 31 points. Jefferson City was second with 69, followed by Branson (77) and Ozark (78). There were 10 teams in the event. 
The sectional meet will be held in Camdenton. ﻿
